            "description": "<div><div class=\"sc-hjefbd ebRREF\"><!--$--><h3 class=\"block core-block\">Gainers</h3><!--/$--><!--$--><ul class=\"block core-block\">\n<li><strong>XWELL</strong> (NASDAQ:<a class=\"ticker\" href=\"https://www.benzinga.com/quote/XWEL\" target=\"_blank\">XWEL</a>) stock increased by 11.1% to $0.86 during Friday's after-market session. The market value of their outstanding shares is at $4.3 million. </li>\n<li><strong>Netclass Technology</strong> (NASDAQ:<a class=\"ticker\" href=\"https://www.benzinga.com/quote/NTCL\" target=\"_blank\">NTCL</a>) stock moved upwards by 10.57% to $1.15. The market value of their outstanding shares is at $24.5 million. </li>\n<li><strong>QVC Group</strong> (NASDAQ:<a class=\"ticker\" href=\"https://www.benzinga.com/quote/QVCGP\" target=\"_blank\">QVCGP</a>) shares rose 9.92% to $3.74. The market value of their outstanding shares is at $45.9 million. </li>\n<li><strong>Aptera Motors</strong> (NASDAQ:<a class=\"ticker\" href=\"https://www.benzinga.com/quote/SEV\" target=\"_blank\">SEV</a>) stock increased by 7.66% to $5.9. The market value of their outstanding shares is at $153.0 million. </li>\n<li><strong>Educational Development</strong> (NASDAQ:<a class=\"ticker\" href=\"https://www.benzinga.com/quote/EDUC\" target=\"_blank\">EDUC</a>) stock rose 6.4% to $1.33. The company's market cap stands at $10.7 million. </li>\n<li><strong>Interactive Strength</strong> (NASDAQ:<a class=\"ticker\" href=\"https://www.benzinga.com/quote/TRNR\" target=\"_blank\">TRNR</a>) stock rose 5.04% to $2.28. The company's market cap stands at $3.6 million. </li>\n</ul><!--/$--><!--$--><h3 class=\"block core-block\">Losers</h3><!--/$--><!--$--><!--/$--><!--$--><p class=\"block core-block\">This article was generated by Benzinga's automated content engine and reviewed by an editor.</p><!--/$--><!--$--><div class=\"sc-fTutPY ljilqG\"></div><!--/$--></div></div>",
